# Screenz – Cursor AI Rules
# Django + MySQL + TMDB Dataset Movie Web App
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

## Project Overview
Screenz is a movie discovery web app built with:
- Backend: Django 4.2 (Python)
- Database: MySQL (via mysqlclient)
- Frontend: Django Templates + Bootstrap 5 + custom CSS/JS
- Data: TMDB 1M movie dataset (CSV import, no live API)
- Auth: Custom user model (email-based login)

## Project Structure
screenz/
├── apps/
│   ├── accounts/     # Custom user model, login, signup, profile
│   ├── movies/       # Movie, Genre, Platform models + views
│   └── watchlist/    # WatchlistItem, WatchedMovie models + AJAX views
├── templates/        # Django HTML templates
│   ├── base.html
│   ├── accounts/
│   ├── movies/
│   ├── partials/     # Reusable template partials (movie_card.html)
│   └── watchlist/
├── static/
│   ├── css/main.css
│   └── js/main.js
├── scripts/
│   └── import_tmdb.py   # TMDB CSV importer
├── data/                # Place TMDB CSV here
├── screenz/
│   ├── settings.py
│   ├── urls.py
│   └── wsgi.py
└── manage.py

## Key Models
- CustomUser (apps.accounts): email login, avatar, bio
- Movie (apps.movies): tmdb_id, title, content_type (movie/tv), genres M2M, platforms M2M, vote_average, release_year, poster_path
- Genre (apps.movies): name, slug
- Platform (apps.movies): name, slug (netflix/prime/jio/hotstar/apple/zee5/sonyliv)
- WatchlistItem (apps.watchlist): user FK, movie FK
- WatchedMovie (apps.watchlist): user FK, movie FK, rating, review

## Coding Conventions
- Use Django class-based views for complex views, function-based for simple ones
- All views require @login_required unless it's the auth page
- Use select_related() and prefetch_related() for all queries with relationships
- Paginate search results at 24 per page
- AJAX calls use fetch() + CSRF token from cookie
- All templates extend base.html (except auth.html which is standalone)
- CSS variables defined in :root for all colors (dark theme)
- Never hardcode colors in templates — use CSS variables

## Database
- MySQL on localhost:3306, database: screenz_db
- Run migrations: python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py migrate
- Import TMDB data: python scripts/import_tmdb.py data/tmdb_movies.csv

## Common Commands
```
python manage.py runserver
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
python scripts/import_tmdb.py data/tmdb_movies.csv
python scripts/import_tmdb.py data/tmdb_movies.csv 10000  # import 10k rows
```

## Design System
- Colors: --accent #E5383B, --bg #0a0a0f, --surface #12121a
- Fonts: Bebas Neue (display/headings), DM Sans (body)
- Dark theme throughout
- Responsive via Bootstrap 5 grid

## Do Not
- Do not use Django REST Framework (not needed — vanilla Django views)
- Do not call TMDB API (blocked in India — use local CSV dataset)
- Do not add new dependencies without updating requirements.txt
- Do not use inline styles in templates — add classes to main.css

## Platform Slugs (canonical)
netflix | prime | jio | hotstar | apple | zee5 | sonyliv
